{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2016-5-9-windows-deleting-node-modules/2016-5-9-windows-deleting-node-modules/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Its my Code Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"26687fc1-7750-5ea1-b951-aab87e3921ba","excerpt":"Windows and node_modules folders When trying to delete a node_modules folder within windows explorer you will be presented with a windows dialog saying the ‘The…","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3a07a1fea255286895be824276a59fe3/a1bbd/delete-node-modules.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.12903225806451%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text \"\n        title=\"Deleting a  \nnode_modules folder on windows\"\n        src=\"/static/3a07a1fea255286895be824276a59fe3/799d3/delete-node-modules.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3a07a1fea255286895be824276a59fe3/00d96/delete-node-modules.png 148w,\n/static/3a07a1fea255286895be824276a59fe3/0b23c/delete-node-modules.png 295w,\n/static/3a07a1fea255286895be824276a59fe3/799d3/delete-node-modules.png 590w,\n/static/3a07a1fea255286895be824276a59fe3/a1bbd/delete-node-modules.png 775w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h1>Windows and node_modules folders</h1>\n<p>When trying to delete a node_modules folder within windows explorer you<br>\nwill be presented with a windows dialog saying the ‘The folder contains items<br>\nwhose names are too long for the Recycle Bin.’ This is due to a restriction<br>\nof the NTFS file system where the MAX_PATH of a complete directory file<br>\npath cannot be more than 260 characters in length.</p>\n<p>As a consequence, when windows tries to move the node_modules folder into<br>\nthe Recycle Bin, the tendency of node dependencies to create multiple<br>\nnested folders and therefore file path names exceeding 260 characters,<br>\nprevents the files from being moved to the recycle bin.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2eed428f96369e5842f6230fe80b7695/a1bbd/long-file-names-node-modules.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.193548387096776%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text \"\n        title=\"Long file names dialog \nwhen deleting a node_modules folder on windows\"\n        src=\"/static/2eed428f96369e5842f6230fe80b7695/799d3/long-file-names-node-modules.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2eed428f96369e5842f6230fe80b7695/00d96/long-file-names-node-modules.png 148w,\n/static/2eed428f96369e5842f6230fe80b7695/0b23c/long-file-names-node-modules.png 295w,\n/static/2eed428f96369e5842f6230fe80b7695/799d3/long-file-names-node-modules.png 590w,\n/static/2eed428f96369e5842f6230fe80b7695/a1bbd/long-file-names-node-modules.png 775w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Deleting node_modules folders on windows</h2>\n<p>When searching online for solutions for deleting a node_modules on windows you can find\nrecommendations to install the excellent <a href=\"https://github.com/isaacs/rimraf\">RimRaf</a>\nutil via npm but you can remove the folders without downloading any utils.</p>\n<h2>Deleting node_modules folders on windows without downloading anything</h2>\n<h3>Steps to follow</h3>\n<h4>Open the windows command prompt</h4>\n<p>Windows start button / type command prompt</p>\n<h4>Change directory to your c drive root</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">cd c:\\</code></pre></div>\n<h4>Create a temp folder</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">mkdir temp</code></pre></div>\n<h4>Use the built in robocopy to remove the node_modules folder that you wish to delete.</h4>\n<p>Tip: you only need to type up to the first three letters of a directory name (depending on\nsimilar directory names) and then you can press tab to autocomplete the name.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">robocopy /MIR c:\\temp c:\\inetpub\\wwwroot\\sample_app\\node_modules</code></pre></div>\n<p><em>robocopy is short for “Robust File Copy” which on from windows vista onwards had replaced\nxcopy.</em> </p>\n<p><em>/MIR is short for Mirror meaning copy (mirror) files from the first folder</em></p>\n<p>This command will have the effect of destroying any files in the second folder that are\nnot present in the first folder.</p>\n<p>So, as you created an empty folder <em>c:\\temp</em> all files within <em>c:\\inetpub\\wwwroot\\sample<em>app<br>\nnode\\</em>modules</em> are not present in <em>c:\\temp</em> and so all files will be deleted (destroyed).</p>\n<h4>Then to delete the empty node_modules folder type</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">RD c:\\inetpub\\wwwroot\\sample_app\\node_modules</code></pre></div>\n<p>Where RD stands for Remove Directory.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Deleting a node_modules folder on windows without downloading anything","date":"May 09, 2016","description":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/2016-5-9-windows-deleting-node-modules/2016-5-9-windows-deleting-node-modules/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2016-4-14-angular2-unit-testing-a-component/2016-4-14-angular2-unit-testing-a-component/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Angular2 - Unit Testing a component"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2016-5-29-the-apple-watch-at-a-glance/2016-5-29-the-apple-watch-at-a-glance/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The Apple Watch at a Glance"}}}}}